title: Woodhead Publishing Series in Biomaterials
description:
[Updated at 2016.03.16]

The books in the extensive Biomaterials series provide comprehensive in depth coverage of advances and key research which is crucial to future development within the field of biomaterials and tissue engineering. Topics covered include: materials, such as polymers, ceramics, metals and glasses; properties, ranging from mechanical properties and biocompatibility to surface science; applications, such as hard or soft tissue engineering; clinical techniques in orthopaedics; and medical device technologies. Titles are edited by biomaterials experts and are ideal for professional researchers and scientists in industry and academia
